Design Elements Breakdown
If you are building this into a web project, here are the technical UI/UX details to keep in mind:

Aspect Ratio Consistency: All product images use the exact same portrait aspect ratio. This is crucial for a clean "alignment" across the row.

The "Mannequin" Choice: Using black, matte mannequins helps the colors of the jerseys pop without the distraction of a human model's face or skin tone. It makes the store feel more like a "pro shop."

Typography Hierarchy:

Product Title: All-caps, bold, black. It uses a high-contrast weight to ensure the user knows exactly what the item is at a glance.

Price: Lighter weight or gray-scale color. It’s secondary to the product name to keep the focus on the "item" first, "cost" second.

Background Uniformity: The black mesh background provides a subtle texture that feels "sporty" and "premium" without being as flat as a plain white studio background.

Spacing (Gutter): There is a consistent 15–20px "gutter" (white space) between each card, which prevents the grid from feeling cluttered.